The Moon God grew disinterested in you and slowly drifted away.
You've become a witness to something beyond your comprehension.\.\.
You've seen something you shouldn't have.
As you slowly regain your consciousness, you realize you're not
the same person as you were still just a brief moment ago.
You wake up to a new reality. Suddenly the dark void above you feels
that much larger, almost infinite. There are things in this world
beyond your understading, beyond human understanding.
You are not sure if this feeling is that of enlightenment or that
of total terror.
The gentle wind on your cheek feels alien. With this newly
acquired understanding, even the most minor sensations have this
altered nuance to them. The moonlight tainted your existence.
But...
At least you survived,\. with your mind still somewhat intact...
You survived...
